node.text:
After nearly 20 years racing at the highest level of the sport, our team decided it’s time to share what we’ve learned with cyclists of all kinds. Now we want to coach you.
 
Years in the making, the Team EF Coaching method eschews dated standards for a dynamic, real-world approach to training. We have developed a dynamic power test and training plan that better prepares riders to meet their goals. We’ve learned from our coaches and our riders about the ups and downs of riding and racing a bike. With Team EF Coaching, we get to share what we’ve learned with you.
 
Head to @teamefcoaching for more.

node.text: Today, Lachlan Morton goes back in time in search of the original Tour spirit. He’ll ride every kilometer of the race — plus the distances between race starts and finishes — solo. He’ll stop at cafés for his food, and sleep under the stars. And he’ll do it all to raise money for @worldbicyclerelief, which gives bikes to students in rural areas of developing countries. Follow his adventure at the link in our bio.

One day @ramonlozano called his friend to mountain bike around his hometown of Girona, Spain. And when he showed up, Lachlan Morton was there to ride along 🤯 

"I already knew who he was," said Lozano. "Since that day, we've seen each other many weekends and sometimes during the week. I show him the hometrails and he helps me with my English and I help him with Spanish. For an amateur like me, it's incredible to share training and adventures with him."

Not a bad deal for either of these guys. Tag your training partner below and let us know what trails you've been exploring these days ⬇️

node.text: “At the beginning, I was more excited to leave home. I still have this feeling. I’m curious. But I’ve realized the more years pass, the more I miss home.” It’s Thursday, so we’re throwing it back to when @albertobettio showed us the art, architecture, and history of Florence.

“It’s satisfying to be smiling on the bike again and contributing to a win.” - @jimmywhelan.jpg

Jimmy Whelan and Neilson Powless made sure that Valgren was first to finish yesterday. This day was extra special for Whelan who came back after suffering two major crashes this past year.

It was great to see you back out there fighting for the win, Jimmy 🤜 🤜 Head to our bio for more on the team's victory in Tuscany.

📷: @fotoreportersirotti

"I could get used to this winning feeling."

Us too, Valgren. Today seems like a pretty good day to announce that he'll be wearing pink again in 2022. We couldn't be more excited for what this Danish Classics pro has got in store 🚲 🚀 🇩🇰 

Head to our bio for more on his extension 🎉

“I dedicate this victory to the whole team. We rode fantastic, so thank you."

Not bad yourself, Valgren. That's TWO wins in two days for the Dane and team 🥇 🥇 

Head to our bio for more from Valgren, Powless, and Whelan on another perfectly executed race in Tuscany 🇮🇹

node.text:
“One just wasn’t enough, huh?” - Ruben Guerreiro to Michael Valgren at the finish.
 
It certainly wasn’t. Neilson Powless and Jimmy Whelan certainly weren’t going to let Valgren go home without another win. Congrats to the whole team on their incredible display of teamwork and power today. Not to mention pulling off back-to-back wins in Tuscany 🇮🇹 🤜

node.text:
The world's fastest race lube has landed. And it’s Ludicrous.

Tested and refined over the last three years by the industry’s leading tribologists and chemists, Ludicrous is taking chain optimization to an entirely new level. We were stoked to have our very own riders involved in testing it earlier this season. Plus we've some big races coming up and know it will be put to good use 🤘 

Head over to @mucoff to find out more.

node.text:
Michael Valgren took his first win in pink today at the Giro della Toscana after beating a star studded field with his perfectly timed attack. This is Valgren's first win since he took the Amstel Gold Race in 2018. 

Today was a special day for a rider that has proved time and time again that he could be there with the best. The team couldn't have worked harder for him — and we couldn't be prouder. Head to our bio now for more.

📷: @fotoreportersirotti
